parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the PTU can cause the vehicle to lose power, hesitate, or roll backwards, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded. It can also damage the rear differential and transmission.
symptoms: The vehicle makes a "pumping" noise
the service 4wd light comes on
the vehicle hesitates or loses power
the vehicle rolls backwards
the emergency collision braking system applies
the engine RPM redlines
the vehicle will not move properly in drive
noise and feeling like the brake is applied.

symptoms: The vehicle hesitates or loses power
the vehicle rolls backwards
the emergency collision braking system applies
the engine RPM redlines
the vehicle will not move properly in drive
noise and feeling like the brake is applied.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Intermittent Noise and Drag on Takeoff
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent noise and drag on takeoff can cause the vehicle to hesitate or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle makes a noise
the vehicle has a drag on takeoff
the vehicle hesitates or loses power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Select-Terrain Traction Management System can cause the vehicle to hesitate or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates or loses power
the Select-Terrain Traction Management System fails to operate as needed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden stalling of the vehicle can cause accidents, especially when it occurs on highways or at intersections, and can leave the driver and other road users at risk of serious harm.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly stops
stalls
or shuts down while driving
often without warning; the vehicle may stall at a light
while driving
or when accelerating or decelerating; the vehicle may not restart immediately.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended stopping of the vehicle can cause accidents, especially when it occurs on highways or at intersections, and can leave the driver and other road users at risk of serious harm.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly stops
often with warning messages or alarms; the vehicle may stop and then resume operation after shifting into park and then back into drive; the vehicle may stop without any warning or error codes.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Safety Recall Notification with No Remedy
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The lack of a remedy for a known safety recall can leave the driver and other road users at risk of serious harm, as the vehicle may be prone to accidents or other safety issues.
symptoms: The manufacturer notifies the owner of a safety recall
but does not provide a remedy or a timeline for resolution; the owner may be left waiting for an extended period for a fix.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The erratic activation of autonomous emergency braking can cause accidents, especially when it occurs on highways or at intersections, and can leave the driver and other road users at risk of serious harm.
symptoms: The vehicle's emergency braking system activates suddenly and without warning
even when there is no vehicle or obstacle in front; the vehicle may slide or go off the road as a result.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Foggy headlights can reduce visibility, making it difficult to drive safely, especially at night or in low-light conditions.
symptoms: Headlights appear foggy or cloudy
reducing illumination
making it difficult to see the road ahead.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Water Infiltration in Turn Signal Housing
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the turn signal can lead to reduced visibility, increasing the risk of accidents, and disabling of advanced safety features such as Lane Departure Warning.
symptoms: Turn signal fails to illuminate
Lane Departure features are disabled
water infiltration in the turn signal housing.
